The attribution operator ( = ) may be used to attribute data to variables. However, there's more to that. The expression  variable = "data"  is itself evaluated to string  "data" .  Likewise, the expression  variable = variable + 5  is evaluated to  variable + 5  and may be shortened to  variable += 5 .  Let's see what kind of assignment expressions we have:     Expression  Translates to  Meaning      x = value  x = value  Assigns  value  to x    x += value  x = x + value  Adds  value  to x    x -= value  x = x - value  Subtracts  value  from x    x *= value  x = x * value  Multiplies x by  value    x /= value  x = x / value  Divides x by  value     Example:  language =  Surge ;
language +=  Script ;
// language now evaluates to  SurgeScript

